TOKYO, March 23 (Reuters) - Mizuho Financial Group Inc (8411.T) said on Wednesday that it plans to form a strategic alliance with Google (GOOGL.O) to serve the Japanese firm's clients more effectively. Under the deal, the Japanese financial group said it aims to utilize Google's know-how to analyze clients' transaction data to improve its customer service quality. It also plans to offer other financial services using Google Cloud platform. Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.